# 1. Project Overview (English)

The objective of this project is to automate Linux server monitoring and reduce downtime through proactive alerting and performance analysis.

The system continuously monitors:

* CPU Utilization
* Memory Usage
* Disk Usage
* Network Health
* Process Status
* Application Availability
* Service Uptime

Alerts are automatically generated when thresholds are exceeded.

Benefits:

* Reduced downtime
* Faster incident response
* Better resource utilization
* Improved system reliability
* Lower operational cost

