# 10. Python Monitoring Script

```python
import psutil
import socket

cpu = psutil.cpu_percent()

memory = psutil.virtual_memory().percent

disk = psutil.disk_usage('/').percent

host = socket.gethostname()

print("Host:", host)

print("CPU:", cpu)

print("Memory:", memory)

print("Disk:", disk)
```

Output

```text
Host: linux01

CPU: 15.5

Memory: 62.3

Disk: 45.1
```

---

# 11. Advanced Monitoring Script

```python
import psutil
import datetime

cpu = psutil.cpu_percent()

memory = psutil.virtual_memory().percent

disk = psutil.disk_usage('/').percent

now = datetime.datetime.now()

log = f"{now} CPU:{cpu} MEM:{memory} DISK:{disk}"

print(log)

with open(
    "monitor.log",
    "a"
) as f:

    f.write(log + "\n")
```

